  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hypertensive patients with moderate hypertension have a risk to develop cardiovascular events
      of 15-20% over a period of 10 years. It is important to reach quickly the advised target, but
      often this result can be obtained with a combination therapy. Some evidences demonstrate
      sartans and calcium channels blockers can be very useful and safe, but it is also important
      to verify which association can give side effects or give some pharmacokinetic interactions
      that can negatively influence the clinical combination efficacy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
